core.sensors

Class QuickChangeFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.sensors.QuickChangeFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Filter

    public class QuickChangeFilter
extends java.lang.Object
implements Filter
    This class serves to remove spiky values in a stream of numbers. It does this by not allowing values that differ to much from previousInputs to pass through the filter.

    • Method Detail

      • filterValue

        public double filterValue(double unfilteredValue)
        This function filters a value from a data stream in two steps. The first step is to compare the unfiltered value to the last returned value. The next one is to compare the unfiltered value to the average value of the last few inputs.
        Specified by:
        filterValue in interface Filter
        Parameters:
        unfilteredValue - The value to be filtered.
        Returns:
        The last input value to pass through the parameters of the filter.
